A skin therapist completes specialized training to provide skincare treatments for clients, typically at spas and physician offices. They perform facial cleansing treatments, laser hair removal, chemical peels, and lymphatic drainage techniques. That is what the delectable and very enchanting beautician, Deborah Enoma from Edo state is into. The entrepreneur who after obtaining a 9-years experience in the financial sector, obtained an MBA in marketing and also a B.Sc. in Library and Information science. The very industrious and hard working Enoma who has been buying and selling since secondary school to LEADERSHIP in an interview that it was her love for business that pushed her into going for an MBA in Marketing. “I run several businesses.. First I’m a perfumer. I got certified in Natural perfumery in Dubai. I’m also a skincare therapist ,also got trained and certified in Dubai. I run a logistics company called Swift Errand Logistics with 7 staff. Still a growing business though…” “I also run a mini spa…I call it mini because we do 3 basic things for now. Facials, Full body scrub and massage,” she revealed while stressing that her company Debskulture is a fast growing company with ” a touch of Debskulture in every home”. Deborah Enoma who also said she’s a motivational speaker also to our correspondent she loves to see people grow.
” I’m motivated by results and I’m a goal getter. Makes me a little bit of a workaholic. I constantly put myself under pressure to work harder. This has also influenced my staff, they  work so hard because we have a committed goal. “We’re making way to get a huge share of the market. And what other way than to be inspired by Dangote. I watch his videos and read a lot about him. My advice to all the youths is have a plan B ,don’t be satisfied with one job, think outside the box and be unique,” she concluded. 